This paper discusses the performance of deep rectifier networks in classification tasks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of geometric symmetries in approximating boundaries, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the issue of compressive representations, which is a topic related to signal processing and information theory (cs.SI).
